#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.40"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.40:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.40:0.2"
msgid "4. Devadūtavagga"
msgstr "4. Messengers from the Gods"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.40:0.3"
msgid "40. Ādhipateyyasutta"
msgstr "40. In Charge"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.148"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.40:1.1"
msgid "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, ādhipateyyāni."
msgstr "“There are, mendicants, these three things to put in charge."

msgctxt "an3.40:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.40:1.3"
msgid "Attādhipateyyaṃ, lokādhipateyyaṃ, dhammādhipateyyaṃ."
msgstr "Putting oneself, the world, or the teaching in charge."

msgctxt "an3.40:1.4"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, attādhipateyyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what, mendicants, is putting oneself in charge?"

msgctxt "an3.40:1.5"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā "
"iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or "
"to an empty hut, and reflects like this:"

msgctxt "an3.40:1.6"
msgid "‘na kho panāhaṃ cīvarahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito."
msgstr ""
"‘I didn’t go forth from the lay life to homelessness for the sake of a robe,"

msgctxt "an3.40:1.7"
msgid ""
"Na piṇḍapātahetu, na senāsanahetu, na itibhavābhavahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajito."
msgstr "alms-food, lodgings, or rebirth in this or that state."

msgctxt "an3.40:1.8"
msgid ""
"Api ca khomhi otiṇṇo jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi "
"domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto."
msgstr ""
"But I was swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, "
"pain, sadness, and distress. I was swamped by suffering, mired in suffering."

msgctxt "an3.40:1.9"
msgid "Appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethāti."
msgstr ""
"And I thought, “Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of "
"suffering.”"

#. VAR: yādisake → yādisake vā (bj, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: vā → ca (mr)
#. VAR: vā → ca (mr)
msgctxt "an3.40:1.10"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana yādisake kāme ohāya agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito tādisake "
"vā kāme pariyeseyyaṃ tato vā pāpiṭṭhatare, na metaṃ patirūpan’ti."
msgstr ""
"But it would not be appropriate for me to seek sensual pleasures like those "
"I abandoned when I went forth, or even worse.’"

msgctxt "an3.40:1.11"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "Then they reflect:"

msgctxt "an3.40:1.12"
msgid ""
"‘āraddhaṃ kho pana me vīriyaṃ bhavissati asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati "
"asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘My energy shall be roused up and unflagging, mindfulness shall be "
"established and lucid, my body shall be tranquil and undisturbed, and my "
"mind shall be immersed in samādhi.’"

msgctxt "an3.40:1.13"
msgid ""
"So attānaṃyeva adhipatiṃ karitvā akusalaṃ pajahati, kusalaṃ bhāveti, "
"sāvajjaṃ pajahati, anavajjaṃ bhāveti, suddhaṃ attānaṃ pariharati."
msgstr ""
"Putting themselves in charge, they give up the unskillful and develop the "
"skillful, they give up the blameworthy and develop the blameless, and they "
"keep themselves pure."

msgctxt "an3.40:1.14"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, attādhipateyyaṃ."
msgstr "This is called putting oneself in charge."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.149"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.40:2.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, lokādhipateyyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what, mendicants, is putting the world in charge?"

