"skillful, they give up the blameworthy and develop the blameless, and they "
"keep themselves pure."

msgctxt "an3.40:3.13"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammādhipateyyaṃ."
msgstr "This is called putting the teaching in charge."

msgctxt "an3.40:3.14"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi ādhipateyyānīti."
msgstr "These are the three things to put in charge.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.40:4.1"
msgid "Natthi loke raho nāma,"
msgstr "“There’s no privacy in the world,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:4.2"
msgid "pāpakammaṃ pakubbato;"
msgstr "for someone who does bad deeds."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:4.3"
msgid "Attā te purisa jānāti,"
msgstr "You’ll know for yourself,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:4.4"
msgid "saccaṃ vā yadi vā musā."
msgstr "whether you’ve lied or told the truth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.40:5.1"
msgid "Kalyāṇaṃ vata bho sakkhi,"
msgstr "When you witness your good self,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:5.2"
msgid "attānaṃ atimaññasi;"
msgstr "you despise it;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:5.3"
msgid "Yo santaṃ attani pāpaṃ,"
msgstr "while you disguise"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:5.4"
msgid "attānaṃ parigūhasi."
msgstr "your bad self inside yourself."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.150"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.40:6.1"
msgid "Passanti devā ca tathāgatā ca,"
msgstr "The gods and the Realized One see"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:6.2"
msgid "Lokasmiṃ bālaṃ visamaṃ carantaṃ;"
msgstr "the fool who lives unjustly in the world."

#. <br>
#. VAR: attādhipateyyako ca → attādhipako sato care (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.40:6.3"
msgid "Tasmā hi attādhipateyyako ca,"
msgstr "So with yourself in charge, live mindfully;"

# Here and below I take nipaka in the sense of “self-controlled”, restrained, or “disciplined”. See my arguments in A Swift Pair of Messengers. The Skt. source gives nipa as “chief”, which fits precisely here next to adhipa. Skt dicts give “wisdom” only from the Pali comms, and I think this should be corrected. Rg Veda has ākenipa, said of the horses of the aśvin-s, “protecting in the vicinity”
#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:6.4"
msgid "Lokādhipo ca nipako ca jhāyī;"
msgstr "with the world in charge, be self-disciplined and practice absorption;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:6.5"
msgid "Dhammādhipo ca anudhammacārī,"
msgstr "with the teaching in charge, live in line with that teaching:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:6.6"
msgid "Na hīyati saccaparakkamo muni."
msgstr "a sage who tries for the truth doesn’t deteriorate."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an3.40:7.1"
msgid "Pasayha māraṃ abhibhuyya antakaṃ,"
msgstr "Māra’s destroyed; the terminator’s overcome:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:7.2"
msgid "Yo ca phusī jātikkhayaṃ padhānavā;"
msgstr "one who strives reaches the end of rebirth."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:7.3"
msgid "So tādiso lokavidū sumedho,"
msgstr "Poised, clever, knowing the world—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:7.4"
msgid "Sabbesu dhammesu atammayo munī”ti."
msgstr "that sage identifies with nothing at all.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.40:7.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.40:7.6"
msgid "Devadūtavaggo catuttho."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an3.40:8.1"
msgid "Brahma ānanda sāriputto,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:8.2"
msgid "Nidānaṃ hatthakena ca;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:8.3"
msgid "Dūtā duve ca rājāno,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:8.4"
msgid "Sukhumālādhipateyyena cāti."
msgstr ""
